===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

# {{rfv-sense}} To [[disgorge]] [[filth]], as a hawk.
# To [[shine]]; to [[glitter]]; to [[glisten]].
#:''The buttons and medals on the soldiers' uniforms '''gleamed''' in the sunlight.''
# To [[radiate]] or [[emanate]] from something.
#:''The delight positively '''gleamed''' from the child as she devoured her cupcake.''
# To be [[briefly]] but [[strongly]] [[apparent]].
#:''The match '''gleamed''' in the dark of the cave, and then went, pitching us into inky blackness.''

====Synonyms====
*(''to shine, glitter, or glisten''): [[glint]], [[sparkle]]
*(''to radiate or emanate''): [[glow]], [[shine]]
*(''to be briefly but strongly apparent''): [[flare]], [[flash]], [[kindle]]

